The paper deals with the problem of learning to reason in first-order logic, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper proposes a new theoretical approach to robustly learning to reason in first-order logic, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cryptography (cs.CR), and logic (cs.LO).
